==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Abear
<hw>A*bear"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>⟦amac⟧beran</ets>; pref. <ets>⟦amac⟧-</ets> + <ets>beran</ets> to
bear.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To bear; to behave.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So did the faery knight himself <qex>abear</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To put up with; to endure.</def>
<mark>[Prov.]</mark> <rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abearance</ent>⟦br⟧
